THE RISK:
{
 "id": "ce-hyperscale-global-split-mirage",
 "title": "CE hyperscale 0.44 is a global-split mirage: Europe's self-build sits in Ireland/Sweden/Belgium, and Frankfurt is colocation",
 "narrative": "The segment axis applies Synergy's GLOBAL capacity split (48% hyperscale × 0.91) to a geography axis built entirely on Central European colocation MW. But CBRE's Europe-specific data says ~60% of operational hyperscaler self-build capacity sits in Ireland, the Netherlands, Sweden and Belgium — three of the four outside CE-7 — and that European colocation 'will remain significantly larger' than hyperscale self-build. Inside CE, hyperscalers show up mostly as TENANTS in Frankfurt and Amsterdam colo halls, where the fit-out and PDU procurement decision often sits with the colo operator or a global tenant framework, not a CE buyer. The model's biggest cell — DE × hyperscale — is therefore substantially phantom, and the true CE mix is inverted toward colocation buyers with different procurement paths.",
 "category": "model-structure",
 "targetNodes": [
  "seg.hyperscale",
  "seg.colocation"
 ],
 "mechanism": [
  {
   "step": "trigger",
   "text": "CBRE Q4-2025: ~60% of Europe's operational hyperscaler self-build capacity is located in Ireland, Netherlands, Sweden, Belgium; and colocation in Europe 'will remain significantly larger' than hyperscaler self-build — the opposite ordering from the model's 0.44 vs 0.18",
   "refs": [
    "digest:seg-mix#c16",
    "digest:seg-mix#c15"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "propagation",
   "text": "The 0.44 was produced by rescaling a raw GLOBAL Synergy share; no Europe- or CE-scoped hyperscale share has ever been observed, and the 'cross-check' (Q1-2025 44% global) is a different quantity that coincidentally matches. Hyperscale demand in CE flows through colo halls whose take-up already outstrips supply",
   "refs": [
    "ledger:seg.hyperscale",
    "digest:seg-mix#c6",
    "digest:seg-mix#c24"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "model-impact",
   "text": "The DE(0.50) × hyperscale(0.44) cell — the largest cell in the cube and the implied beachhead for selling to large operators — is largely phantom in CE; weight belongs in colocation, whose buyer, spec and procurement cadence differ from what the venture is building for",
   "refs": [
    "ledger:geo.DE",
    "ledger:seg.colocation",
    "profile:Who is the primary buyer you'll sell through first?"
   ]
  }
 ],
 "whyMissable": "seg.hyperscale carries maturity 'triangulated' with multiple Synergy vintages agreeing on trajectory — it looks like the best-sourced segment node. The agreement is real but among GLOBAL figures; nothing in the ledger flags that the quantity was never observed at European scope, and Frankfurt's AI headlines make 'hyperscale dominates CE' feel confirmed daily.",
 "expectedObviousness": "low",
 "falsifier": "A Europe- or CE-scoped capacity split (CBRE, Synergy regional cut, or EUDCA country tables) showing hyperscale-owned capacity at ≥40% of CE-7 total data-center capacity.",
 "likelihood": {
  "value": 0.58,
  "rationale": "CBRE's Europe-specific reporting directly contradicts the global ordering, and the cross-corpus tension flags that no CE-scoped hyperscale share exists; the open question is only magnitude, not direction. [evidence revision: The specific CBRE Q4-2025 figure (60% of self-build in IE/NL/SE/BE and colocation ~50% larger than self-build) is now directly confirmed by an independent secondary source, strengthening both load-bearing premises about geographic mislocation and colo-vs-hyperscale ordering. However, no source directly quantified the CE-7 hyperscale-owned share, so the magnitude of the 'phantom' DE×hyperscale cell remains inferential — a modest upward revision is warranted, not a large one.]",
  "basis": "evidence",
  "revisedFrom": 0.5
 },
 "perturbation": [
  {
   "nodeId": "seg.hyperscale",
   "op": "set",
   "value": 0.28,
   "note": "CE hyperscale-owned share far below global 0.44; self-build concentrated outside CE-7"
  },
  {
   "nodeId": "seg.colocation",
   "op": "set",
   "value": 0.32,
   "note": "Mix-shift: the displaced weight lands in colocation, per CBRE's European ordering"
  }
 ],
 "indicators": [
  {
   "signal": "Europe hyperscale self-build vs colocation GW split, updated quarterly",
   "where": "CBRE 'Europe Data Centres' quarterly figures report; DCD coverage of CBRE releases",
   "threshold": "CE-7 hyperscale self-build share reported <30% of CE capacity",
   "updates": "increases"
  },
  {
   "signal": "Country-level ownership mix (colocation/hyperscale/enterprise) for DE and NL",
   "where": "EUDCA 'State of European Data Centres' annual report country tables",
   "threshold": "Germany capacity shown as majority colocation-operated",
   "updates": "increases"
  }
 ],
 "mitigations": [
  {
   "action": "Commission a CE-scoped ownership split (hyperscale-owned vs colo vs enterprise MW for the CE-7) before locking segment-weighted GTM targets",
   "type": "information",
   "voiNodeId": "seg.hyperscale",
   "note": "Replaces the rescaled global split with an observed regional quantity"
  },
  {
   "action": "Build the launch spec and reference designs around colocation operators and their fit-out integrators rather than hyperscaler direct accounts",
   "type": "strategic",
   "voiNodeId": null,
   "note": "Aligns product qualification with the segment that actually dominates CE"
  }
 ],
 "evidenceStatus": "corroborated",
 "evidence": [
  {
   "title": "CBRE: European hyperscaler self-build capacity growth to outpace colocation supply growth",
   "sourceType": "industry-report",
   "publisher": "DatacenterDynamics / CBRE",
   "date": "2026-02-20",
   "excerpt": "60 percent of Europe’s operational hyperscale self-build capacity located in Ireland, the Netherlands, Sweden, and Belgium... The colocation segment is expected to remain about 50 percent larger than the self-build segment at the end of 2026.",
   "url": "https://www.datacenterdynamics.com/en/news/cbre-european-hyperscaler-self-build-capacity-growth-to-outpace-colocation-supply-growth-but-supply-outpaces-take-up-in-weaker-than-expected-2025/",
   "attached": true
  },
  {
